result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Attorney Christopher R Smith in court.   Defendant Koua Moua did not appear.   Pablo Galaviz appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  State moves to have this case dismissed and read-in to 14CT976, Court grants the State's motion.

Defendant Koua Moua in court with attorney Christopher R Smith.  Abbey Nickolie appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Defendant should have his license by the next date.  Hearing scheduled for May 29, 2015 at 09:00 am.

Defendant is not to operate a motor vehicle unless properly licensed.    Defendant not to possess any drug paraphernalia.  Defendant is not to use/possess any controlled substances without a valid prescription and take as prescribed.    Defendant to comply with I.D. Processing.

Defendant Koua Moua in court with attorney Christopher R Smith.   District Attorney's Office Law Intern appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Alex Lee sworn.
Atty. Smith requests a date at the end of April for the defendant to obtain his license.    NOT GUILTY PLEA ENTERED.
DEFENDANT NEEDS ID PROCESSING.  Hearing scheduled for May 1, 2015 at 10:30 am.
Adjourned initial appearance on March 30, 2015 at 09:00 am.

Attorney Christopher R Smith in court.   Defendant Koua Moua did not appear.   Brian J. Juech appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Interpreter Alex Lee in Court.
Atty. Smith states he was informed that his client was in the hospital and provides documentation to the Court.  Court tries to contact the defendant.
Defendant to be present by video or in person at the next hearing.  Adjourned initial appearance scheduled for March 30, 2015 at 09:00 am.
Bail/bond hearing on March 16, 2015 at 10:30 am.

Attorney Christopher R Smith in court.   Defendant Koua Moua did not appear.   Bryan C. Bayer appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Alex Lee in court.
